High-ranking Russian military officers who committed war crimes in Bucha and Mariupol were to be targeted: "We know who you are, you will not get away with this." Sberbank, Russia's largest bank, is to be disconnected from the SWIFT bank transfer system. Three big state-owned Russian broadcasters are to be cut off from the European Union on cable, satellite or the internet as what she called "mouthpieces that amplify Putin's lies". Von der Leyen said the EU was also announcing an end to its dependency on Russian oil: "It will not be easy but we simply have to do it." All Russian oil will be phased out, she said, but in an orderly fashion. Crude oil will be phased out in six months and refined products by the end of 2022, she said. --BBC-- 